          "title": "The systematic decapitation of Judah's leadership",
          "body": "The narrator records three categories of leadership removal: military (the king captured and blinded, 25:5-7; the army scattered, 25:5), cultic (the chief priest Seraiah and second priest Zephaniah executed at Riblah, 25:18-21), and civil (officials, royal advisers, and sixty civic leaders executed, 25:19-21). This is not collateral damage — it is the deliberate dismantling of every institution through which the covenant had been administered in Judah. The king is gone. The priests are dead. The civil administrators are executed. What remains (25:12) is the poorest of the land, kept not for their value to God but for their utility to Babylon as agricultural laborers. The covenant community has been functionally annihilated at the leadership level. Jeremiah, who survived (Jer. 40:1-6), was the only prophetic voice left standing in the land."
